{{iPhone models}}
'''iPhone 15 Pro''' and '''iPhone 15 Pro Max''' are to be released products in the [[iPhone]] line of [[Smartphone|smartphones]] made by [[Apple Inc.|Apple]] which are to be released sometime in between September 15, 2023 and October 7, 2023.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=iPhone 15: Everything We Know |url=https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/iphone-15/ |access-date=2022-09-02 |website=MacRumors |language=en}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web |last=Livemint |date=2022-10-11 |title=iPhone 15: How a note to Apple Store employees may have leaked its launch date |url=https://www.livemint.com/technology/gadgets/iphone-15-how-a-note-to-apple-store-employees-may-have-leaked-its-launch-date-11665465018083.html |access-date=2022-10-11 |website=mint |language=en}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite web |last=gargi.chaudhry |title=iPhone 15 launched date leaked? Here's what we know so far |url=https://newsable.asianetnews.com/gadget-technology/apple-iphone-15-launched-date-leaked-here-is-what-we-know-so-far-gcw-rjkvve |access-date=2022-10-11 |website=Asianet News Network Pvt Ltd |language=en}}</ref><ref name=":3">{{Cite web |title=Apple iPhone 15 launch date reportedly leaked by Apple Store employee |url=https://www.dnaindia.com/technology/report-apple-iphone-15-launch-date-reportedly-leaked-by-apple-store-employee-2991931 |access-date=2022-10-11 |website=DNA India |language=en}}</ref><ref name=":4">{{Cite web |date=2022-10-10 |title=iPhone 15 release date LEAKED? Just check this out |url=https://tech.hindustantimes.com/mobile/news/iphone-15-release-date-leaked-just-check-this-out-71665414549452.html |access-date=2022-10-11 |website=HT Tech |language=en}}</ref> These phones are to be released with [[iOS 17]], which is in the [[iOS]] line of software made by [[Apple Inc.|Apple]].

== Design ==

=== Solid-state Buttons ===

iPhone 15 Pro and iPhone 15 Pro Max may have solid-state buttons. Solid-state buttons are buttons that provide feedback via The Taptic Engine, which is Apple's branding for haptic motors.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kelly |first=Gordon |title=New Apple Leak Reveals iPhone 15 Design Shock |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/gordonkelly/2022/10/31/apple-iphone-15-pro-max-ultra-taptic-solid-state-buttons/ |access-date=2022-11-01 |website=Forbes |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Livemint |date=2022-10-30 |title=Apple iPhone 15 Pro models may borrow this design feature from iPhone 8, SE 3 |url=https://www.livemint.com/technology/gadgets/iphone-15-pro-models-may-borrow-this-design-feature-from-iphone-8-se-3-11667099345092.html |access-date=2022-11-01 |website=mint |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Staff |first=News9 |date=2022-10-31 |title=Apple might ditch mechanical buttons for haptic feedback on iPhone 15 Pro variants |url=https://www.news9live.com/technology/mobile-phone/apple-might-ditch-mechanical-buttons-for-haptic-feedback-on-iphone-15-pro-variants-205040 |access-date=2022-11-01 |website=NEWS9LIVE |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=iPhone 15 Pro, 15 Pro Max to ditch physical buttons for solid-state buttons: Apple analyst Ming-Chi Kuo |url=https://www.financialexpress.com/industry/technology/iphone-15-pro-15-pro-max-to-ditch-physical-buttons-for-solid-state-buttons-apple-analyst-ming-chi-kuo/2760064/ |access-date=2022-11-01 |website=Financialexpress |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=iPhone 15 Pro models tipped to ditch physical button design, here is what we know |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/technology/news/story/iphone-15-pro-models-tipped-to-ditch-physical-button-design-here-is-what-we-know-2290446-2022-10-28 |access-date=2022-11-01 |website=India Today |language=en}}</ref>

=== Charging Port ===
The whole iPhone 15 lineup may be switching to USB-C because of the EU regulations.<ref name=":6" /><ref name=":7" /><ref name=":8" /><ref name=":9" /><ref name=":10" />

